# quack-auth project conventions

**Source of truth** for coding and layout conventions in this repo.

When the Developer states a **new convention**:

1. Update **this file** with the full convention text.
2. Add a **one-line pointer** in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) only ‚Äî do not duplicate detail there.

## Shared DTOs (`libs/dtos/src/lib/<domain>/`)

Organize by **domain folder** (e.g. `user/`, not flat files at `lib/` root unless legacy).

| Suffix | Purpose | Example |
| ------ | ------- | ------- |
| **`.model.ts`** | Zod mirror of a **persisted** Mongoose model (stored shape only; no plaintext passwords) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/user.model.ts` |
| **`.dto.ts`** | Flow/API schemas (signup, login, responses, ‚Ä¶) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/signup.dto.ts` |

- **Model DTO** (`.model.ts`) reflects what is stored in the database ‚Äî not plaintext passwords or other transient input shapes.
- **Other DTOs** (`.dto.ts`) hold API/input validation (e.g. signup with plaintext password rules).
- Reuse shared Zod building blocks inside a domain (e.g. `password.schema.ts`) when multiple DTOs need the same rules.
- NestJS wraps shared schemas with `createZodDto` in `apps/BE` ‚Äî keep wrappers in sync when adding schemas (see `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/06-nestjs-zod.md`).

## Mongoose (`mongoose/models/<domain>/`)

Per domain, always three files:

| File | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| **`*.schema.ts`** | Mongoose schema + `model()` registration |
| **`*.model.ts`** | Repository interfaces (`IUser`, `IUserDocument`, ‚Ä¶) |
| **`*.paths.ts`** | Field path constants for queries, projections, and schema keys |

### Why `*.paths.ts`?

**Never hard-code field strings** in queries ‚Äî import from `*.paths.ts` so renames touch one file.

Example:

```ts
import { UserPaths } from 'mongoose/models/user';

UserModel.findOne({ [UserPaths.email]: email });
```

### Mongoose directory (root)

```
mongoose/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ client.ts          # DB connection (ENV_KEYS, E2E URI switch)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ models/            # domain folders (user/, ‚Ä¶)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fixtures/          # test/dev fixture data
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tsconfig.json
```

## Imports

- `@shared/dtos`, `@shared/constants` from apps and `mongoose/`
- App-local: `@/*` under `apps/FE` or `apps/BE`
- App tsconfigs: `baseUrl: "../.."` and extend `./tsconfig.json` (FE must keep `jsx`)

## Workflow

- New chat ‚Üí `./scripts/next-quack-branch.sh <slug>` ‚Üí `quack-XX-<slug>`
- Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, ‚Ä¶) ‚Äî enforced by commitlint; do not commit unless asked
- Verify with `pnpm check` or targeted `tsc` when touching types
